        <task xml:id="voting-into-gardening1">
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Who will be elected Master?  What percent of the vote will he or she have? <fillin characters="10" />
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    D, with <m>\frac{5}{14}\approx 35.7\%</m>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </task>
        <task xml:id="voting-into-gardening2">
            <statement>
                <p>
                    As you look at the voters' preferences,
                    who seems like the best choice to make the most voters happy? <fillin characters="10" />
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    G because they seem to be either first or second choice to nearly all voters.
                </p>
            </solution>
        </task>
        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    If your answers to <xref ref="voting-into-gardening1"/> and 
                    <xref ref="voting-into-gardening2"/> are different, can you explain why? <fillin characters="10" />
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    The answers should be different. Since G is nearly everyone's second choice, they are a better candidate than 
                    D who is listed last or next to last for everyone except those putting D first.
                </p>
            </solution>
        </task>
